Annie E. KAVANAUGH, alias, Defendant, Appellant, v. James D. McQUAID, Trustee, Plaintiff, Appellee. Circuit Court of Appeals, First Circuit. January 14, 1929. No. 2236. E. M. Shanley and Benjamin Tannenbaum, both of Boston, Mass., for appellant. James R. Flanagan, of Boston, Mass., for appellee.

Before BINGHAM, JOHNSON, and ANDERSON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It is ordered that this ease be, and the same hereby is, dismissed for want of prosecution.
